.TH SINGINE-CONTEXT 1 "2026-03-13" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-context \- inspect terminal context and sourced environment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine context
[\fB--shell\fR \fBbash\fR|\fBsh\fR] [\fB--json\fR] [\fB--glossary-root\fR \fIPATH\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Shows the current terminal context, sourced shell environment markers, and
glossary-backed definitions used by Singine to distinguish live runtime state
from inherited shell setup.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --shell
Report context for a specific shell shape.
.TP
.B --json
Emit structured JSON output.
.TP
.B --glossary-root \fIPATH\fR
Override the glossary package root.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine context
singine context --json
singine context --shell bash
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1),
.BR singine-runtime (1),
.BR singine-snapshot (1)
